When launching a token on a DeFi platform, it's essential to ensure you have all necessary components in place to facilitate the token sale and subsequent listing on a launchpad. Below are the steps you can follow to achieve this:

### 1. Create a Token Sale Contract
A token sale contract is crucial for selling your tokens to early investors. You can create this contract using Ethereum's Solidity programming language. Here's a basic example:

```solidity
pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

contract TokenSale {
    uint256 tokenAmount;
    function sale() public payable {
        tokenAmount = msg.value;
        tokenAmount -= msg.value;
        payable(msg.sender, tokenAmount);
    }
}
```

### 2. Create a Launchpad Token Sale Contract
